==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From German ''[[Pudel]]'', short for ''[[Pudelhund]]'', from Low German ''[[pudeln]]'' ‘to splash about’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈpu:dəl/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#Any of various [[breed]]s of [[dog]] originating in [[Europe]] as [[hunt]]ing dogs, and having heavy, curly [[fur]] in a solid color; their shoulder height indicates their classification as standard, miniature, or toy.

